OL,3,CResurfaced roads to be relaid again
OL,4,Cafter fault in tarmac
OL,6,FSteve Roussel, General Manager at
OL,7,FRonez Ltd, told ITV News: "We monitor
OL,8,Fthe roads after they are laid, just to
OL,9,Fmake sure that there aren't any issues
OL,10,Fand this just came out of routine
OL,11,Fmonitoring.
OL,13,F"We could just see that there was an
OL,14,Fissue with some of the stones starting
OL,15,Fto strip out of the asphalt that has
OL,16,Fbeen laid, which you wouldn't expect
OL,17,Fthat early on."
OL,19,FThere are not thought to be any
OL,20,Fimmediate safety concerns. However,
OL,21,Fthe roads will need to be relaid.
